UMLCanvas is an implementation around the HTML5 Canvas that allows
generation of UML diagrams. A Mediawiki extension is provided to allow
editors to just enter the commands required to generate the
diagrams. Two interfaces are provided: an OO Javascript API and a
textual DSL in the form of a UML profile for ADL, the Application
Definition Language.

UMLCanvas is a project by TheSoftwareFactory, 
maintained by Christophe VG <xtof@thesoftwarefactory.be>

* Kickstart

# ls
LICENSE		README		doc		lib		src
Makefile	TODO		examples	samples
# make
*** generating adl parser for the web
*** assembling UmlCanvas
*** assembling UmlCanvas extesion

--> take a look at the html files in the examples directory

If you have rhino installed, check out the CLI samples:

# make adl-run
*** cloning prototype repository
*** building minimal prototype support for testing
*** generating adl parser
*** running adl parser on samples/class.adl
class TestClass +stereotype="entity" {
  attribute Attribute1: Integer +visibility="public";
  attribute Attribute2: String +visibility="private";
  attribute Attribute3: Boolean +visibility="protected";
  method Method1: Integer +visibility="public" {
    argument param1: Integer[20];
    argument param2: String[1..2];
  }
  method Method2: Boolean +visibility="protected" {
    argument param1: Object;
    argument param2: Something;
  }
}
Visiting root
Visiting TestClass : root
Visiting Attribute1 : TestClass
Visiting Attribute2 : TestClass
Visiting Attribute3 : TestClass
Visiting Method1 : TestClass
Visiting param1 : Method1
Visiting param2 : Method1
Visiting Method2 : TestClass
Visiting param1 : Method2
Visiting param2 : Method2

Install the extension:

# cd /var/www/htdocs/mediawiki-install-dir/extensions
# ln -s /path/to/build/extensions/umlcanvas 
# echo 'require_once( "$IP/extensions/umlcanvas/umlcanvas.php" );' \
    >> LocalSettings.php
